content.text:
- **Title:** CDK12/13 Inhibitor :: Carrick Therapeutics, Inc.
  - **URL:** `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/pipeline/cdk1213-inhibitor`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “## CT7439: CDK12/13 inhibitor/Cyclin-K Degrader”
    - “CT7439 is a CDK12/13/Cyclin-K degrader, which potently inhibits the cellular activity of CDK12/13.”
    - “The compound acts as an inhibitor of CDK12 but also as a 'glue degrader' of Cyclin-K” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/pipeline/cdk1213-inhibitor))

- **Title:** Carrick Therapeutics Announces U.S. FDA Clearance of IND for CT7439, a First-In-Class Inhibitor of CDK12/13 (PDF)
  - **URL:** `https://d1io3yog0oux5.cloudfront.net/_d4fcdc3f1eef88e32cfe969a2cfa8e3c/carricktherapeutics/news/2023-09-07_Carrick_Therapeutics_Announces_U_S_FDA_Clearance_20.pdf`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “(FDA) has cleared the Company’s Investigational New Drug (IND) application for CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor.”
    - “CT7439 is an inhibitor of CDK12/13 as well as a 'glue degrader' of Cyclin-K” ([d1io3yog0oux5.cloudfront.net](https://d1io3yog0oux5.cloudfront.net/_d4fcdc3f1eef88e32cfe969a2cfa8e3c/carricktherapeutics/news/2023-09-07_Carrick_Therapeutics_Announces_U_S_FDA_Clearance_20.pdf))

- **Title:** Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor) (PDF)
  - **URL:** `https://d1io3yog0oux5.cloudfront.net/_d4fcdc3f1eef88e32cfe969a2cfa8e3c/carricktherapeutics/news/2024-09-23_Carrick_Therapeutics_Announces_First_Patient_25.pdf`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor / Cyclin-K glue-degrader.”
    - “Clinical trial details can also be found onwww.clinicaltrials.gov under study ID: NCT06600789.” ([d1io3yog0oux5.cloudfront.net](https://d1io3yog0oux5.cloudfront.net/_d4fcdc3f1eef88e32cfe969a2cfa8e3c/carricktherapeutics/news/2024-09-23_Carrick_Therapeutics_Announces_First_Patient_25.pdf))

- **Title:** Posters & Publications :: Carrick Therapeutics, Inc.
  - **URL:** `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/science/posters-publications`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “CT7439 an oral first-in class selective CDK12/13 Inhibitor and Cyclin K degrader: Mechanistic profiling and combination efficacy in an ovarian cancer model”
    - “Identification of an orally bioavailable dual Cyclin-K glue degrader – CDK12/13 inhibitor’” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/science/posters-publications))

- **Title:** A Modular Phase 1/2 Study With CT7439 in Participants With Solid Malignancies (NCT06600789) - ICH GCP
  - **URL:** `https://ichgcp.net/clinical-trials-registry/NCT06600789`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “Clinical Trial NCT06600789”
    - “Intervention / Treatment  *  Drug: CT7439 Capsules (0.5 mg, 1mg, 3mg)”
    - “Other Study ID Numbers  *  CT7439_001” ([ichgcp.net](https://ichgcp.net/clinical-trials-registry/NCT06600789))

- **Title:** Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer - PubMed
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “Here we report the development of SR-4835, a highly selective dual inhibitor of CDK12 and CDK13, which disables triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC) cells.”
    - “Here we report the development of SR-4835” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))

- **Title:** Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor - PubMed
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “we have synthesized a potent PROTAC degrader PP-C8”
    - “Importantly, PP-C8 demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with PARP inhibitor in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC).” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))

- **Title:** Discovery of a Highly Potent and Selective Dual PROTAC Degrader of CDK12 and CDK13 - PubMed
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “The optimal compound 7f effectively degraded CDK12 and CDK13 with DC_{50} values of 2.2 and 2.1 nM”
    - “7f markedly inhibited proliferation of multiple TNBC cell lines including MFM223” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/))

- **Title:** Discovery of ZLC491 as a Potent, Selective, and Orally Bioavailable CDK12/13 PROTAC Degrader - PMC
  - **URL:** `https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11513923/`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “we report the discovery of ZLC491 as a potent, selective, and orally bioavailable CDK12/13 PROTAC degrader.”
    - “ZLC491 efficiently degraded CDK12 and CDK13 with DC_{50} values of 32 and 28 nM, respectively, in TNBC MDA-MB-231 cells.” ([pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11513923/))

- **Title:** The CDK inhibitor CR8 acts as a molecular glue degrader that depletes cyclin K - PubMed
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32494016/`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “we identify CR8-a cyclin-dependent kinase (CDK) inhibitor^{6}-as a compound that acts as a molecular glue degrader.”
    - “a complex between CDK12-cyclin K and the CUL4 adaptor protein DDB1” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32494016/))

  - **URL:** `https://patents.google.com/patent/US11666578B2/fr`
  - **Direct quotes:**
    - “Publication number  US11666578B2”
    - “Small molecule inhibitors of CDK12/CDK13” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/US11666578B2/fr))
